<paragraph blockId="15.[132,1237,1689,1790]" pageId="15">
The postdefecating larva of this species (fig. 7) is almost identical to that of 
<taxonomicName box="[1004,1236,1689,1715]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Lestrimelitta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="glabrata">
<emphasis box="[1004,1236,1689,1715]" italics="true" pageId="15">Lestrimelitta glabrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(fig. 7) described above, although the apical breadth of the mandible may be slightly wider and tapers to blunt (non-spoon-shaped) apex (fig. 32B).
</paragraph>
